<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Octavia_V._Rogers_Albert" title="Octavia V. Rogers Albert">Albert, Octavia V. Rogers</a>. <i>The House of Bondage Or Charlotte Brooks and Other Slaves</i>. Oxford University Press, 1991. Primary sources with commentary. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0195067843" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-506784-3</a>
<ul>
<li><i><a href="http://docsouth.unc.edu/neh/albert/albert.html" class="external text" title="http://docsouth.unc.edu/neh/albert/albert.html" rel="nofollow">The House of Bondage, or, Charlotte Brooks and Other Slaves, Original and Life-Like</a></i> complete text of original 1890 edition, along with cover &amp; title page images, at website of <a href="/wiki/University_of_North_Carolina_at_Chapel_Hill" title="University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill">University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Berlin, Ira, Joseph P. Reidy, and Leslie S. Rowlands, eds. <i>Freedom: A Documentary History of Emancipation, 1861-1867</i> 5 vol Cambridge University Press, 1982. very large collection of primary sources regarding the end of slavery</li>
<li>Blassingame, John W., ed. <i>Slave Testimony: Two Centuries of Letters, Speeches, Interviews, and Autobiographies</i>.Louisiana State University Press, 1977.</li>
