<li>"The Heroic Slave." <i>Autographs for Freedom</i>. Ed. Julia Griffiths Boston: Jewett and Company, 1853. 174-239. Available at the Documenting the American South website<a href="http://docsouth.unc.edu/neh/douglass1853/menu.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://docsouth.unc.edu/neh/douglass1853/menu.html" rel="nofollow">[6]</a>.</li>
<li>Frederick Douglass <i><a href="/wiki/My_Bondage_and_My_Freedom" title="My Bondage and My Freedom">My Bondage and My Freedom</a></i> (1855) (Project Gutenberg: <a href="http://www.gutenberg.net/etext/202" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.gutenberg.net/etext/202" rel="nofollow">[7]</a>)</li>
